{{champion:84}} {{champion:150}} {{champion:64}} {{champion:55}} {{champion:429}} {{champion:421}} {{champion:58}} {{champion:107}} {{champion:92}} {{champion:157}} {{champion:238}} {{champion:76}} 


All of these champions are highly mobile with no cost at all for it. I can handle when a mobile champion uses mana or an ult to get to me, but people that are mobile for no cost at all and have high damage and dueling power like all of these people do? No thank you... 

Do not remove mobility just make it a high risk/ reward. If you want to be mobile it should cost a lot, which also leaves a meaningful window of weakness for your enemy. And stop making new champions with good damage, cc, engage/disengage AND slap in high mobility. Rito pls

replies.body:
{{champion:107}} and {{champion:58}} aren't exactly what I would call mobile, and I definitely wouldn't rank them up there with {{champion:84}}  and {{champion:64}} 

Rengar has to be near a bush to use his one, TARGETED dash. The only other time he can use it is with his ult, which gives you a decent warning. "!"

Renekton has two shitty, short-range dashes, and he has to hit the first one to even use the second one anyway.

Why isn't Kalista up there? Just because she has a mana bar doesn't mean she actually uses it cause you know...Q= up to 70 mana W=25 mana for sight and 25 mana might aswell be nothing. E is free cause of that mana return. and having a no CD passive dash is the most delinquent thing I've seen.

